This set applies in addition to restrictions contained in these ToS.\u003c/td>\u003c/tr>\u003ctr>\u003ctd>\"Plan\"\u003c/td>\u003ctd>means any licensing model offered to you by Ruptly via Website.\u003c/td>\u003c/tr>\u003ctr>\u003ctd>\"Pool Materials\"\u003c/td>\u003ctd>means Videos and/or Livestreams for free distribution from various third parties made available to you on the terms set out in clause 5 of these ToS.\u003c/td>\u003c/tr>\u003ctr>\u003ctd>\"Term\"\u003c/td>\u003ctd>means the period of time for which Content is licensed to you by Ruptly subject to Plan chosen by you or Ruptly Content License Agreement.\u003c/td>\u003c/tr>\u003ctr>\u003ctd>\"Website\"\u003c/td>\u003ctd>means\u003c!-- --> \u003ca href=\"/en/\">ruptly.tv\u003c/a> \u003c!-- -->and its sub domains.\u003c/td>\u003c/tr>\u003c/tbody>\u003c/table>\u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ch2>Content.\u003c/h2>\u003cp>Ruptly is offering different types of Content available to the customers via Website:\u003c/p>\u003col>\u003cli>Videos and/or Livestreams in 2D dimensional format (hereinafter jointly referred to as \"\u003cb>Standard Content\u003c/b>\") produced by Ruptly or licensed to us by third parties.\u003c/li>\u003cli>Videos and/or Livestreams in 360 \"spherical\" format (hereinafter jointly referred to as \"\u003cb>360-Content\u003c/b>\") produced by Ruptly or licensed to us by third parties.\u003c/li>\u003c/ol>\u003c/li>\u003cli>\u003ch2>Pool Materials.\u003c/h2>\u003col>\u003cli>Ruptly may from time to time provide \"Pool Materials\" on its Website as an additional service. Such models (Plans) are:\u003c/p>\u003col>\u003cli>\u003cp>\"\u003cb>Ruptly Pass\u003c/b>\"\u003c/p>\u003ch3>Applicability\u003c/h3>\u003cp>Ruptly Pass will only be offered for any teams or entities who operate no more than two digital platforms which should meet following requirements:\u003c/p>\u003cul>\u003cli>up to 150,000 total page likes, followers and subscribers across two nominated Social Pages or Channels;\u003c/li>\u003c/ul>\u003cp>OR\u003c/p>\u003cul>\u003cli>one website with up to 90,000 total site Sessions or similar metrics (A session is the period of time a user is actively engaged with your website. Note: some Analytical tools call \"Sessions\" as \"Visits\".) for the last 90 days and one Social page or Channel up to 100,000 likes, followers or subscribers.\u003c/li>\u003c/ul>\u003cp>Every unique customer can have only one valid Ruptly Pass at any given time period. Ruptly reserves the right to terminate (with immediate effect and without refunding any license fees) any Ruptly Pass agreement concluded by the customer if the data we have available allow us to conclude unambiguously that Ruptly Pass has already been purchased by this customer earlier.\u003c/p>\u003ch3>Qualification and providing access\u003c/h3>\u003cp>You have to specify these two digital platforms during the ordering process accurately. After payment for the Ruptly Pass, Ruptly has to qualify the specified digital platforms. In order to qualification you shall submit to Ruptly Screenshot of the Google Analytics or your Analytical tool Dashboard (Unfiltered view) for the last 90 days. Screenshot should be sent to\u003c!-- --> \u003ca href=\"mailto:pass@ruptly.tv\">pass@ruptly.tv\u003c/a>.\u003c/p>\u003cp>The Screenshot of the Google Analytics or your Analytical tool should contain following or similar data for the last 90 days:\u003c/p>\u003cul>\u003cli>Users – Users who have initiated at least one session during the date range.\u003c/li>\u003cli>Sessions – Total number of Sessions within the date range. A session is the period of time a user is actively engaged with your website. Note: some Analytical tools call \"Sessions\" as \"Visits\".\u003c/li>\u003cli>Bounce Rate – The percentage of single-page sessions in which there was no interaction with the page. A bounced session has a duration of 0 seconds.\u003c/li>\u003cli>Session Duration – The average length of a session.\u003c/li>\u003cli>Top Active Pages – The most popular pages on your website.\u003c/li>\u003c/ul>\u003cp>Qualification can take up to one working day. You will be informed of the outcome of qualification via e-mail specified by you during registration:\u003c/p>\u003cul>\u003cli>in case of successful qualification you will be provided with access to the Content and Pool Materials promptly;\u003c/li>\u003cli>in case of failure to qualify you will be entitled to a refund of the fee you paid, such refund shall be made using the payment method originally used by you to make your purchase.\u003c/li>\u003c/ul>\u003ch3>Common conditions applicable to Ruptly Pass\u003c/h3>\u003cp>\u003cb>Term\u003c/b>: subscription period of minimum one year.\u003c/p>\u003cp>\u003cb>Renewal\u003c/b>: automatic renewal of the subscription period every 12 months from the Commencement date.
